LECTURE: Energy is a vital part of our daily lives. We use energy to keep warm, to cook our food, to run our appliances, and to power our cars.
Where does energy come from?

Work is a way of using energy to make something happen. For example, when you lift a heavy object, you do work on the object. You use energy to move the object against the force of gravity.

LECTURE: A chemical change is a change in which the type of matter changes.
Matter is changed into a different type of matter.
Some chemical changes are caused by heating or cooling. For example, burning a piece of paper is a chemical change caused by heating. When paper gets hot enough, it re­acts with oxygen in the air and burns. The paper and oxygen change into ash and smoke.
A physical change is a change in which the type of matter stays the same.
Matter is changed into a different type of the same matter.
